input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: TOWN HALL OF ASNIERES SUR SEINE. Summary: Supply and Delivery of Personalized Support Checks and Gift Vouchers for the City of Asnieres-Sur-Seine. Description: The purpose of this consultation is: The purpose of this consultation is the acquisition and supply of personalized support vouchers (CAP) and gift vouchers. The CAPs are intended to support beneficiaries within the framework of social assistance schemes of the Municipal Center of Social Action of the City of Asnieres-sur-Seine. The CAP will be used in accordance with current regulations to enable the purchase of basic necessities (food and hygiene), to the exclusion of any products such as tobacco, alcohol or games. Gift vouchers, multi-brands, are aimed at young graduates living in the town of Asnieres-sur-Seine. These checks must allow purchase in any department. They constitute financial aid allowing the winners to acquire the equipment necessary to pursue their studies in higher education. In addition, the city is likely to use a certain number of these gift vouchers as part of events rewarding Asnierois. In a command group with the Municipal Social Action Center of the city of Asnieres-sur-Seine (CCAS). The town of Asnieres-sur-Seine is the coordinator of the group. The City of Asnieres-sur-Seine and its attached establishment (CCAS) are indifferently referred to as the city of Asnieres-sur-Seine in the documents. The description of the services to be carried out are specified within the C.C.T.P.. Published Date: 2025-11-06. Closing Date: 2025-12-04. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

Description: The purpose of this framework agreement is the purpose of the printing and supply of documents of small and medium formats intended for institutional communication from the Pays de la Loire region (leaflets type publishing documents, brochures, cards ... but also small or medium format posters) except Communication documents relating to the regional transport network (Aleop) which are subject to a separate framework agreement. The framework agreement takes effect from 19/01/2026 or the date of notification if it is later. It is concluded for a period of 12 months renewable 3 times per Tacitus renewal for a new period of 12 months without its duration being able to exceed 48 months. The framework agreement is mixed (article R2162-3 of the public procurement code); He can therefore perform by means of orders on the basis of the prices indicated in the unit price slip but also by means of subsequent markets which may be: either at a global and flat -rate price; either at unit prices; or at mixed prices. The framework agreement is mono-attribute. The minimum and maximum cumulative amounts of orders and subsequent markets that can be carried out within the framework of this Framework agreement are defined as follows: minimum amount: 10,000 euros HTVA for 12 months; Maximum amount: 100,000 euros HTVA for 12 months.. Published Date: 2025-07-16. Closing Date: 2025-09-09. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed
